1. Launch an Ec2 instance and install and start docker
2. create a dir for your project, create a Docker and HTML file
3. Build docker image and run it in a detached mode with the command (docker run -d -p 80:80 --name project-container project-image.
4. copy your public IP address and run it on GUI
5. create a ECR, create a IAM role, attach permission and login on your terminal
6. Authenticate your AWS with AccessKey and SecretKey
7. login your ECR on your terminal and tag your image, then push to Amazon ECR.

8. Create an Application Load Balancer
9. create a Task definition and create a cluster
10. create a service in the cluster

sudo snap install aws-cli --classic


